@startuml data-flow
title undef-terminal — Data Flow Through the System

skinparam backgroundColor #ffffff
skinparam defaultFontColor #333333
skinparam arrowColor #2563eb
skinparam componentBorderColor #d1d5db
skinparam componentBackgroundColor #f3f4f6
skinparam noteBorderColor #d1d5db
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #f9fafb
skinparam packageBorderColor #d1d5db
skinparam packageBackgroundColor #ffffff
skinparam databaseBorderColor #d1d5db
skinparam databaseBackgroundColor #f3f4f6

package "Remote / Local Process" {
  [PTY / Shell\nSSH / Telnet] as PTY
}

package "Worker (CLI / uterm share)" {
  [Worker Process\n(undef-terminal connector)] as WP
}

package "Server (TermHub)" {
  [Worker WebSocket\nbearer token auth] as WWS
  [TermHub\nbroker + session state] as HUB
  [DeckMux Mixin\nPresenceStore + TransferManager] as DMX
  [Browser WebSocket\nJWT role auth] as BWS
}

package "Browser" {
  [xterm.js\nterminal renderer] as XTERM
  [DeckMux\nTS coordinator] as DMTS
  [Presence Bar\navatars + colors] as BAR
  [Edge Indicators\nminimap bars] as EDGE
  [Cursor Overlay\npins + selections] as OVERLAY
}

PTY --> WP : raw bytes
WP --> WWS : **control stream framing**\nDLE(0x10) + STX(0x02)\nheader before payload

note right of WWS
  Binary channels
  (tunnel protocol):
  0x00 = control (JSON)
  0x01 = terminal (PTY bytes)
  0x02 = TCP tunnel
  0x03 = HTTP inspection
end note

WWS --> HUB : authenticated frames\nrouted by channel byte
HUB --> DMX : presence_update\ncontrol_request\ncontrol_transfer
HUB --> BWS : terminal bytes → all browsers
DMX --> BWS : presence messages\n(ride same WebSocket)

BWS --> XTERM : terminal bytes\n(channel 0x01)
BWS --> DMTS : presence JSON\n(channel 0x00 control)

DMTS --> BAR : avatar state\n(name, color, role)
DMTS --> EDGE : viewport positions\n(scroll_line per user)
DMTS --> OVERLAY : pins, selections,\ncursor positions

database "PresenceStore\n(server)" as PSS
database "Keystroke Queue\n(TransferManager)" as KQ

DMX --> PSS : store / sync user state
DMX --> KQ : buffer keystrokes\nduring idle countdown

note bottom of HUB
  Lock never held across
  network I/O (TOCTOU-safe).
  All hub methods are public;
  private state: _lock, _workers.
end note

@enduml
